<TITLE> Curfew relaxes for Monday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 26 (bdnewss24.com)  The government has relaxed the curfew for Monday from 5am to 12 midnight in six divisional cities, including Dhaka, a top police officer said Sunday. Dhaka metropolitan police commissioner Naim Ahmed told bdnews24.com that the curfew would come back in force after Monday midnight. In the backdrop of Dhaka University incidents, the emergency government enforced a curfew in six divisional cities, including Dhaka, from 8pm Wednesday, which lingered into a fifth day, Sunday, with occasional breaks. bdnew
